# Core Framework

## Definition
Plasticity is not growth.  
It is susceptibility to change.

## Levels
- Macro: major life/system shocks (trauma, war, parenthood)
- Meso: structured inputs (habits, education, therapy, systems)
- Micro: short-lived states (sleep, emotion, novelty)

## Core Principle
Systems do not change uniformly.  
Plasticity emerges unevenly across time and structure.

## Working Thesis
To understand change, you must observe systems when they are destabilized—but not yet reorganized. 